      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk man the \"statistical likelihood\" thing doesnt explain everything. like yesterday i typed \"why is the...\" and it suggested \"why is the red car outside\" even though i didnt even type the word red or car. i dont even own a red car. it was just... there. sitting there in the suggestions like it knew exactly what was happening outside my window in real time. how does a \"trend\" or \"aggregated data\" know what's happening in my driveway right this second? it felt way too intentional for just being math.",
